nd his wife are the founders of the luke and meadow foundation a philanthropic cause that focuses on children controversyedit on february   france endorsed donald trump as a candidate in the  election for the new president of the united states it was controversial due to nascars decision from the previous july to pull its xfinity series and camping world truck series award ceremonies from a trump resort near miami in the wake of the businessman’s comments about mexican immigrants  referencesedit  mark spoor turner sports interactive  brian france named nascar chairman ceo  september   nascarcom retrieved    darrell waltrip  brian france time   a b c thomas durso spring  taking stock of nascar pdf family business –   a b jim francis  the history of nascar crabtree publishing company p  retrieved september     a b paul biedryzycki  spring march  giving no breaks dujour magazine p    kevin conley  nascars new track the new yorker   a b liz clarke  one helluva ride how nascar swept the nation random house pp – retrieved september     rick horrow karla swatek  beyond the box score morgan james publishing isbn    a b c rick horrow karla swatek  beyond the box score an insiders guide to the  billion business of sports wordclay p    clarke   jim pedley randy covitz  a racing family fields of thunder the story of the kansas speedway kansas city star books p  retrieved september     nascar  popular mechanics march  p  retrieved september     nate ryan november   in  years brian france has revamped nascar usa today retrieved september     clarke   clarke   jim peltz july   brian france is trying to keep nascar relevant los angeles times retrieved february     jack gage  nascars trouble at the track forbes   gluck jeff march   nascar ceo brian france some drivers endorse donald trump for president usa today retrieved april    external linksedit luke and meadow foundation website v t e the france family of nascar first generation bill france sr second generation bill france jr j