epartment where he endeavoured to grow the products youth audience and began to move the company away from its title sponsor winston cigarettes in order to facilitate this his final position before becoming ceo was executive vicepresident he was also on the board of directors ceo of nascaredit in  france was named nascars chairman of the board and ceo by his father who preceded him one of his first actions was to create a new rule that drivers were no longer allowed to race back to the startfinish line when under caution after assuming control of nascar france negotiated a title sponsorship from sprint nextel he also introduced the chase for the sprint cup over the transition period receiving a  billion television contract for the initial ten race seasons in addition to a later multibilliondollar deal with nbc part of the chase was to award more points to significant or spectacular wins instead of consistent winning as nascar had previously done introducing it as a form of postseason for the sport he also made an effort to expand the audience base of nascar to minorities and allowed toyota vehicles to begin competing on the nascar circuit he has also overseen nascar during a period of ratings drops as well as attendance going down  over the period of his tenure despite record television deals other venturesedit france also owns brand sense partners a los angelesbased licensing company that launched britney spears’ line of perfume he and his wife are the founders of the luke and meadow foundation a philanthropic cause that focuses on children controversyedit on february   france endorsed donald trump as a candidate in the  election for the new president of the united states it was controversial due to nascars decision from the previous july to pull its xfinity series and camping world truck series award ceremonies from a trump resort near miami in the wake of the businessman’s comments about mexican immigrants  referencesedit  mark spoor turner sports interactive  brian france named nascar chairman ceo  september   nascarcom retrieved    darrell waltrip  brian france time   a b c thomas durso spring  taking stock of nascar pdf family business –   a b jim francis  the history of nascar crabtree publishing company p  retrieved september     a b paul biedryzycki  spring march  giving no breaks dujour magazine p    kevin conley  nascars new track the new yorker   a b liz clarke  one helluva ride how nascar swept the nation random house pp – retrieved september     rick horrow karla swatek  beyond the box score morgan james publishing isbn    a b c rick horrow karla swatek  beyond the box score an insiders guide to the  billion business of sports wordclay p    clarke   jim pedley randy covitz  a racing family fields of thunder the story of the kansas speedway kansas city star books p  retrieved september     nascar  popular mechanics march  p  retrieved september     nate ryan november   in  years brian france has revamped nascar usa today retrieved september     clarke   clarke   jim peltz july   brian france is trying to keep nascar relevant los angeles times retrieved february     jack gage  nascars trouble at the track forbes   gluck jeff march   nascar ceo brian france some drivers endorse donald trump for president usa today retrieved april    external linksedit luke and meadow foundation website v t e the france family of nascar first generation bill france sr second generation bill france jr jim france third generation brian france lesa kennedy j c france fourth generation ben kennedy v t e nascar chairmen and presidents bill france sr bill france jr mike helton brian france major national racing series monster energy nascar cup series daytona  xfinity series camping world truck series regional  local racing series kn pro series east west whelen modified whelen modified tour whelen southern modified tour weekly short track racing whelen allamerican series international series nascar australia nascar in australia auscar nasca